<br>
Richard Matheson. <br>
<br>
His most famous works are Hell House (There's a movie with Rowdy McDowell which lacks considerably in atmosphere but has the basic concept down) and I Am Legend which inspiried two movies The Omega Man with Charlton Heston (typical 70's work that makes Matheson appear like a hack, in other words, not worth your money) and Planet of the Vampires which pretty much sucks too. Apparently there's a new one in the works that people want Will Smith for. Hey, whatever, just as long as it doesn't suck I'm cool with that.<br>
<br>
Also, Anne Rice fans should probably check out Poppy Z Brite, though at times she reads like typical goth writings, she's got some decent stories and atmosphere in her writings, though she falls into the same pitfall as Rice does and most of her characters are remarkably similiar to each other. I wonder if she ever got that sex change she wanted?<br>
<br>
If you don't mind orgies and the like, Bentley Little is actually an excellent writer in my opinion. Very much likes to use ancients gods and goddess in his/her novels. <br>
<br>
And if your not pretentious to chalk comic books as kiddie stuff get Preacher, or well damn near anything from Vertigo. Amazing works to choose from. Sandman, Hellblazer, and there three billion assorted mini-series like Dhampyr, Mythos: The Last Tour, The Girl Who Would Be Death and the ilk.<br>
<br>
Good hunting. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/emoticons_classic/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
